OL,3,CHillsborough campaigner who lost his
OL,4,Cson in the tragedy has died
OL,6,FMrs Hammond said: "Hopefully you can
OL,7,Funderstand how much we miss him. We
OL,8,Fwere certainly blessed to have such a
OL,9,Flovely boy, even though it was for
OL,10,Fonly 14 short years. We still miss him
OL,11,Fvery much."
OL,13,FIn September, Prime Minister Sir Keir
OL,14,FStarmer said the Government would
OL,15,Fbring forward a Hillsborough Law by
OL,16,Fthe time of the next anniversary of
OL,17,Fthe disaster, in April, to force
OL,18,Fpublic bodies to co-operate with
OL,19,Finvestigations into major disasters or
OL,20,Fpotentially face criminal sanctions.
